E.COLI 0157:H7 IN SCHOOLCHILDREN - JAPAN (2)
============================================
[See: E. coli 0157:H7 - Japan: RFI archive.960614]
Date: Mon, 17 Jun 1996 22:18:00 +0900
From: <MHH00326@niftyserve.or.jp>

This is from local newspaper, CHUGOKU-SHINBUN.
June 13:
--------
HIROSHIMA
---------
On June 7, an 8-year-old boy got fever, abdominal pain,
and bloody diarrhea. He was hospitalized to Miyoshi Central
Hospital on June 10 and _E.coli_ 0157 was detected from his stool.
He is now getting well.
On June 12, 65 cases of food poisoning were reported from the
students of Tojyo Elementary School, Tojyo town, Hiroshima Prefecture.
3 were hospitalized.
June 14:
---------
10 new cases (total 145) were reported. 11 recovered,
39 still sick.
June 15:
---------
11 new cases (total 156) were reported. 19 recovered.
31 still sick, 4 in hospital.

15 samples (total 21) were proved to be 0157 positive.
The investigation team is trying to find the cause of the
infection. 200 food samples used by the school lunch after May 20 and
[from] its production facilities are under investigation.
The Ministory of Health and Welfare warned of the spread of the
EHEC 0157 infection and advised the following precautions:
_E.coli_ is sterilized by 1 minute at 75 degrees centigrade.
1. Cook thoroughly if beef or pork meal is suspected to be contaminated.
2. Wash hands and cooking appliances thoroughly.
3. Those who have bloody diarrhea, especially infants, should
consult a doctor.
June 17:
-------
HIROSHIMA
---------
On June 16, the first case of secondary infection of _E.coli_ was
reported from Tojo-cho town, Hiroshima. _E.coli_ 0157 was detected
in the younger sister of the student of Tojo elementary school.
She is 6 years old, complained the slight stomachache and
has now recovered.
On June 16, 0157 was detected from 16 new cases.
11 were students and 5 were teachers of the school.
In total, 0157 was detected from 31 students, 5 teachers, and
1 kindergarten child.
The lunch was compared with the former Okayama Oku-cho school lunch,
but the only common foods between them were sauce and ketchup.
The source of the infection is still unknown.
The 0157 food poisoning is spreading.
AICHI
-----
The 0157 food poisoning was reported from Takamoridai Junior
High School, Kasugai City, Aichi Prefecture. 21 students complain
of sickness and 0157 was detected in 8 students. 15 were
recovered and 6 recovering. Investigation of the source
was done but 0157 was not yet found.

OKAYAMA
-------
New mass food poisoning was reported from elementary and junior high
schools in NIIMI city, OKAYAMA. Total of 20 students complain of diarrhea
and bloody stool. 0157 infection were suspected.
--
H.Kikuchi
Hiroshima Quarantine Station, Japan
MHH00326@niftyserve.or.jp
